Global Funds Purchase Net 16 Billion Rupees of India Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-02-14T03:39:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/global-funds-purchase-net-16-billion-rupees-of-india-derivatives.html
Global funds bought a net 16 billion
rupees ($350 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on Feb. 11,
according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 3.4 percent to 974.5 billion rupees, or 34.4
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 5.38 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on Feb. 11, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
